{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This is Shivdutt Yadav,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and he's from Uttar Pradesh, India."},{"time":6000,"text":"Now Shivdutt was visiting the local land registry office"},{"time":9000,"text":"in Uttar Pradesh,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and he discovered"},{"time":13000,"text":"that official records were listing him as dead."},{"time":15000,"text":"His land was no longer registered"},{"time":17000,"text":"in his name."},{"time":19000,"text":"His brothers, Chandrabhan and Phoolchand,"},{"time":22000,"text":"were also listed as dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24000,"text":"Family members had bribed officials"},{"time":26000,"text":"to interrupt the hereditary transfer of land"},{"time":29000,"text":"by having the brothers declared dead,"},{"time":31000,"text":"allowing them to inherit"},{"time":33000,"text":"their father's share of the ancestral farmland."},{"time":36000,"text":"Because of this, all three brothers and their families"},{"time":39000,"text":"had to vacate their home."},{"time":42000,"text":"According to the Yadav family,"},{"time":44000,"text":"the local court has been scheduling a case review"},{"time":46000,"text":"since 2001,"},{"time":48000,"text":"but a judge has never appeared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"There are several instances in Uttar Pradesh"},{"time":53000,"text":"of people dying"},{"time":55000,"text":"before their case is given a proper review."},{"time":58000,"text":"Shivdutt's father's death and a want for his property"},{"time":61000,"text":"led to this corruption."},{"time":64000,"text":"He was laid to rest in the Ganges River,"},{"time":66000,"text":"where the dead are cremated along the banks of the river"},{"time":68000,"text":"or tied to heavy stones and sunk in the water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"Photographing these brothers"},{"time":74000,"text":"was a disorienting exchange"},{"time":76000,"text":"because on paper they don't exist,"},{"time":78000,"text":"and a photograph is so often used as an evidence of life."},{"time":81000,"text":"Yet, these men remain dead."},{"time":84000,"text":"This quandary led to the title of the project,"},{"time":86000,"text":"which considers in many ways"},{"time":89000,"text":"that we are all the living dead"},{"time":91000,"text":"and that we in some ways represent"},{"time":93000,"text":"ghosts of the past and the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"So this story is the first of 18 chapters"},{"time":100000,"text":"in my new body of work titled \"A Living Man Declared Dead and Other Chapters.\""},{"time":105000,"text":"And for this work,"},{"time":107000,"text":"I traveled around the world over a four-year period"},{"time":109000,"text":"researching and recording bloodlines"},{"time":111000,"text":"and their related stories."},{"time":114000,"text":"I was interested in ideas surrounding fate"},{"time":117000,"text":"and whether our fate is determined"},{"time":119000,"text":"by blood, chance or circumstance."},{"time":124000,"text":"The subjects I documented"},{"time":126000,"text":"ranged from feuding families in Brazil"},{"time":128000,"text":"to victims of genocide in Bosnia"},{"time":130000,"text":"to the first woman to hijack an airplane"},{"time":132000,"text":"and the living dead in India."},{"time":135000,"text":"In each chapter, you can see the external forces"},{"time":138000,"text":"of governance, power and territory or religion"},{"time":141000,"text":"colliding with the internal forces"},{"time":143000,"text":"of psychological and physical inheritance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"Each work that I make"},{"time":149000,"text":"is comprised of three segments."},{"time":151000,"text":"On the left are one or more portrait panels"},{"time":154000,"text":"in which I systematically order"},{"time":156000,"text":"the members of a given bloodline."},{"time":158000,"text":"This is followed by a text panel, it's designed in scroll form,"},{"time":161000,"text":"in which I construct"},{"time":163000,"text":"the narrative at stake."},{"time":165000,"text":"And then on the right is what I refer to as a footnote panel."},{"time":168000,"text":"It's a space that's more intuitive"},{"time":170000,"text":"in which I present fragments of the story,"},{"time":172000,"text":"beginnings of other stories, photographic evidence."},{"time":175000,"text":"And it's meant to kind of reflect"},{"time":178000,"text":"how we engage with histories or stories on the Internet,"},{"time":180000,"text":"in a less linear form."},{"time":182000,"text":"So it's more disordered."},{"time":184000,"text":"And this disorder is in direct contrast"},{"time":187000,"text":"to the unalterable order of a bloodline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"In my past projects I've often worked in serial form,"},{"time":195000,"text":"documenting things that have"},{"time":197000,"text":"the appearance of being comprehensive"},{"time":199000,"text":"through a determined title and a determined presentation,"},{"time":202000,"text":"but in fact, are fairly abstract."},{"time":205000,"text":"In this project I wanted to work in the opposite direction"},{"time":207000,"text":"and find an absolute catalog,"},{"time":210000,"text":"something that I couldn't interrupt, curate or edit by choice."},{"time":214000,"text":"This led me to blood."},{"time":216000,"text":"A bloodline is determined and ordered."},{"time":219000,"text":"But the project centers"},{"time":221000,"text":"on the collision of order and disorder --"},{"time":223000,"text":"the order of blood butting up against the disorder"},{"time":226000,"text":"represented in the often chaotic and violent stories"},{"time":229000,"text":"that are the subjects of my chapters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"In chapter two, I photograph the descendants of Arthur Ruppin."},{"time":236000,"text":"He was sent in 1907 to Palestine"},{"time":239000,"text":"by the Zionist organization"},{"time":241000,"text":"to look at areas for Jewish settlement"},{"time":244000,"text":"and acquire land for Jewish settlement."},{"time":247000,"text":"He oversaw land acquisition"},{"time":249000,"text":"on behalf of the Palestine Land Development Company"},{"time":252000,"text":"whose work led to the establishment"},{"time":254000,"text":"of a Jewish state."},{"time":257000,"text":"Through my research at the Zionist Archives in Jerusalem,"},{"time":260000,"text":"I wanted to look at the early paperwork"},{"time":262000,"text":"of the establishment of the Jewish state."},{"time":264000,"text":"And I found these maps which you see here."},{"time":267000,"text":"And these are studies"},{"time":269000,"text":"commissioned by the Zionist organization"},{"time":271000,"text":"for alternative areas for Jewish settlement."},{"time":273000,"text":"In this, I was interested in the consequences"},{"time":275000,"text":"of geography"},{"time":277000,"text":"and imagining how the world would be different"},{"time":279000,"text":"if Israel were in Uganda,"},{"time":282000,"text":"which is what these maps demonstrate."},{"time":284000,"text":"These archives in Jerusalem,"},{"time":286000,"text":"they maintain a card index file"},{"time":288000,"text":"of the earliest immigrants and applicants for immigration"},{"time":291000,"text":"to Palestine, and later Israel,"},{"time":293000,"text":"from 1919 to 1965."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"Chapter three:"},{"time":300000,"text":"Joseph Nyamwanda Jura Ondijo"},{"time":303000,"text":"treated patients outside of Kisumu, Kenya"},{"time":306000,"text":"for AIDS, tuberculosis, infertility,"},{"time":309000,"text":"mental illness, evil spirits."},{"time":311000,"text":"He's most often paid for his services"},{"time":314000,"text":"in cash, cows or goats."},{"time":317000,"text":"But sometimes when his female patients"},{"time":319000,"text":"can't afford his services,"},{"time":321000,"text":"their families give the women to Jura"},{"time":324000,"text":"in exchange for medical treatment."},{"time":326000,"text":"As a result of these transactions,"},{"time":328000,"text":"Jura has nine wives,"},{"time":330000,"text":"32 children"},{"time":332000,"text":"and 63 grandchildren."},{"time":334000,"text":"In his bloodline you see the children and grandchildren here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"Two of his wives were brought to him"},{"time":341000,"text":"suffering from infertility"},{"time":343000,"text":"and he cured them,"},{"time":346000,"text":"three for evil spirits,"},{"time":348000,"text":"one for an asthmatic condition and severe chest pain"},{"time":351000,"text":"and two wives Ondijo claims he took for love,"},{"time":354000,"text":"paying their families a total of 16 cows."},{"time":357000,"text":"One wife deserted him"},{"time":359000,"text":"and another passed away during treatment for evil spirits."},{"time":363000,"text":"Polygamy is widely practiced in Kenya."},{"time":366000,"text":"It's common among a privileged class"},{"time":368000,"text":"capable of paying numerous dowries"},{"time":370000,"text":"and keeping multiple homes."},{"time":372000,"text":"Instances of prominent social and political figures"},{"time":375000,"text":"in polygamous relationships"},{"time":377000,"text":"has led to the perception of polygamy"},{"time":380000,"text":"as a symbol of wealth, status and power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"You may notice in several of the chapters that I photographed"},{"time":388000,"text":"there are empty portraits."},{"time":390000,"text":"These empty portraits represent individuals,"},{"time":392000,"text":"living individuals, who couldn't be present."},{"time":395000,"text":"And the reasons for their absence are given in my text panel."},{"time":398000,"text":"They include dengue fever,"},{"time":400000,"text":"imprisonment, army service,"},{"time":402000,"text":"women not allowed to be photographed"},{"time":404000,"text":"for religious and cultural reasons."},{"time":407000,"text":"And in this particular chapter,"},{"time":409000,"text":"it's children whose mothers"},{"time":411000,"text":"wouldn't allow them to travel to the photographic shoot"},{"time":413000,"text":"for fear that their fathers would kidnap them during it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"Twenty-four European rabbits"},{"time":421000,"text":"were brought to Australia in 1859"},{"time":423000,"text":"by a British settler"},{"time":425000,"text":"for sporting purposes, for hunting."},{"time":428000,"text":"And within a hundred years,"},{"time":430000,"text":"that population of 24 had exploded to half a billion."},{"time":434000,"text":"The European rabbit has no natural predators in Australia,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and it competes with native wildlife"},{"time":439000,"text":"and damages native plants"},{"time":441000,"text":"and degrades the land."},{"time":443000,"text":"Since the 1950s,"},{"time":445000,"text":"Australia has been introducing lethal diseases"},{"time":448000,"text":"into the wild rabbit population"},{"time":450000,"text":"to control growth."},{"time":452000,"text":"These rabbits were bred at a government facility,"},{"time":455000,"text":"Biosecurity Queensland,"},{"time":457000,"text":"where they bred three bloodlines of rabbits"},{"time":459000,"text":"and have infected them with a lethal disease"},{"time":461000,"text":"and are monitoring their progress"},{"time":463000,"text":"to see if it will effectively kill them."},{"time":466000,"text":"So they're testing its virulence."},{"time":468000,"text":"During the course of this trial, all of the rabbits died,"},{"time":471000,"text":"except for a few, which were euthanized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"Haigh's Chocolate,"},{"time":476000,"text":"in collaboration"},{"time":478000,"text":"with the Foundation for Rabbit-Free Australia,"},{"time":481000,"text":"stopped all production of the Easter Bunny in chocolate"},{"time":484000,"text":"and has replaced it with the Easter Bilby."},{"time":487000,"text":"Now this was done to counter"},{"time":489000,"text":"the annual celebration of rabbits"},{"time":491000,"text":"and presumably make the public more comfortable"},{"time":493000,"text":"with the killing of rabbits"},{"time":495000,"text":"and promote an animal that's native to Australia,"},{"time":497000,"text":"and actually an animal that is threatened"},{"time":499000,"text":"by the European rabbit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503000,"text":"In chapter seven, I focus on the effects"},{"time":505000,"text":"of a genocidal act"},{"time":507000,"text":"on one bloodline."},{"time":509000,"text":"So over a two-day period,"},{"time":511000,"text":"six individuals from this bloodline"},{"time":513000,"text":"were killed in the Srebrenica massacre."},{"time":515000,"text":"This is the only work"},{"time":517000,"text":"in which I visually represent the dead."},{"time":519000,"text":"But I only represent those"},{"time":521000,"text":"that were killed in the Srebrenica massacre,"},{"time":523000,"text":"which is recorded as the largest mass murder in Europe"},{"time":526000,"text":"since the Second World War."},{"time":529000,"text":"And during this massacre,"},{"time":531000,"text":"8,000 Bosnian Muslim men and boys"},{"time":533000,"text":"were systematically executed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536000,"text":"So when you look at a detail of this work,"},{"time":539000,"text":"you can see, the man on the upper-left"},{"time":541000,"text":"is the father of the woman sitting next to him."},{"time":543000,"text":"Her name is Zumra."},{"time":545000,"text":"She is followed by her four children,"},{"time":548000,"text":"all of whom were killed in the Srebrenica massacre."},{"time":551000,"text":"Following those four children is Zumra's younger sister"},{"time":554000,"text":"who is then followed by her children"},{"time":556000,"text":"who were killed as well."},{"time":559000,"text":"During the time I was in Bosnia,"},{"time":561000,"text":"the mortal remains of Zumra's eldest son"},{"time":563000,"text":"were exhumed from a mass grave."},{"time":565000,"text":"And I was therefore able to photograph"},{"time":567000,"text":"the fully assembled remains."},{"time":569000,"text":"However, the other individuals"},{"time":571000,"text":"are represented by these blue slides,"},{"time":573000,"text":"which show tooth and bone samples"},{"time":575000,"text":"that were matched to DNA evidence collected from family members"},{"time":578000,"text":"to prove they were the identities"},{"time":580000,"text":"of those individuals."},{"time":582000,"text":"They've all been given a proper burial,"},{"time":584000,"text":"so what remains are these blue slides"},{"time":586000,"text":"at the International Commission for Missing Persons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"These are personal effects"},{"time":593000,"text":"dug up from a mass grave"},{"time":595000,"text":"that are awaiting identification from family members"},{"time":598000,"text":"and graffiti at the Potochari battery factory,"},{"time":601000,"text":"which was where the Dutch U.N. soldiers were staying,"},{"time":604000,"text":"and also the Serbian soldiers later"},{"time":606000,"text":"during the times of the executions."},{"time":610000,"text":"This is video footage used at the Milosevic trial,"},{"time":612000,"text":"which from top to bottom"},{"time":614000,"text":"shows a Serbian scorpion unit"},{"time":616000,"text":"being blessed by an Orthodox priest"},{"time":619000,"text":"before rounding up the boys and men"},{"time":621000,"text":"and killing them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"Chapter 15 is more of a performance piece."},{"time":629000,"text":"I solicited China's State Council Information Office in 2009"},{"time":633000,"text":"to select a multi-generational bloodline"},{"time":636000,"text":"to represent China for this project."},{"time":639000,"text":"They chose a large family from Beijing for its size,"},{"time":642000,"text":"and they declined to give me"},{"time":644000,"text":"any further reasoning for their choice."},{"time":646000,"text":"This is one of the rare situations"},{"time":648000,"text":"where I have no empty portraits."},{"time":650000,"text":"Everyone showed up."},{"time":652000,"text":"You can also see the evolution of the one-child-only policy"},{"time":655000,"text":"as it travels through the bloodline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659000,"text":"Previously known as the Department of Foreign Propaganda,"},{"time":662000,"text":"the State Council Information Office"},{"time":665000,"text":"is responsible for all of China's external publicity operations."},{"time":669000,"text":"It controls all foreign media and image production"},{"time":672000,"text":"outside of China"},{"time":674000,"text":"from foreign media working within China."},{"time":676000,"text":"It also monitors the Internet"},{"time":678000,"text":"and instructs local media"},{"time":680000,"text":"on how to handle any potentially controversial issues,"},{"time":683000,"text":"including Tibet, ethnic minorities,"},{"time":686000,"text":"Human Rights, religion,"},{"time":688000,"text":"democracy movements and terrorism."},{"time":691000,"text":"For the footnote panel in this work,"},{"time":694000,"text":"this office instructed me"},{"time":696000,"text":"to photograph their central television tower in Beijing."},{"time":699000,"text":"And I also photographed the gift bag they gave me"},{"time":701000,"text":"when I left."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"These are the descendants of Hans Frank"},{"time":709000,"text":"who was Hitler's personal legal advisor"},{"time":712000,"text":"and governor general of occupied Poland."},{"time":715000,"text":"Now this bloodline includes numerous empty portraits,"},{"time":718000,"text":"highlighting a complex relationship"},{"time":720000,"text":"to one's family history."},{"time":723000,"text":"The reasons for these absences"},{"time":725000,"text":"include people who declined participation."},{"time":728000,"text":"There's also parents who participated"},{"time":731000,"text":"who wouldn't let their children participate"},{"time":733000,"text":"because they thought they were too young to decide for themselves."},{"time":736000,"text":"Another section of the family"},{"time":738000,"text":"presented their clothing, as opposed to their physical presence,"},{"time":741000,"text":"because they didn't want to be identified"},{"time":743000,"text":"with the past that I was highlighting."},{"time":745000,"text":"And finally, another individual"},{"time":747000,"text":"sat for me from behind"},{"time":749000,"text":"and later rescinded his participation,"},{"time":751000,"text":"so I had to pixelate him out so he's unrecognizable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"In the footnote panel that accompanies this work"},{"time":759000,"text":"I photographed an official Adolph Hitler postage stamp"},{"time":763000,"text":"and an imitation of that stamp"},{"time":765000,"text":"produced by British Intelligence"},{"time":767000,"text":"with Hans Frank's image on it."},{"time":769000,"text":"It was released in Poland"},{"time":771000,"text":"to create friction between Frank and Hitler,"},{"time":773000,"text":"so that Hitler would imagine"},{"time":775000,"text":"Frank was trying to usurp his power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779000,"text":"Again, talking about fate,"},{"time":781000,"text":"I was interested in the stories and fate"},{"time":783000,"text":"of particular works of art."},{"time":785000,"text":"These paintings were taken by Hans Frank"},{"time":788000,"text":"during the time of the Third Reich."},{"time":790000,"text":"And I'm interested in the impact of their absence and presence through time."},{"time":794000,"text":"They are Leonardo da Vinci's \"Lady With an Ermine,\""},{"time":797000,"text":"Rembrandt's \"Landscape With Good Samaritan\""},{"time":800000,"text":"and Raphael's \"Portrait of a Youth,\""},{"time":802000,"text":"which has never been found."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"Chapter 12 highlights"},{"time":808000,"text":"people being born into a battle that is not of their making,"},{"time":811000,"text":"but becomes their own."},{"time":813000,"text":"So this is the Ferraz family"},{"time":815000,"text":"and the Novaes family."},{"time":817000,"text":"And they are in an active blood feud."},{"time":820000,"text":"This feud has been going on since 1991"},{"time":823000,"text":"in Northeast Brazil in Pernambuco,"},{"time":826000,"text":"and it involved the deaths"},{"time":828000,"text":"of 20 members of the families"},{"time":830000,"text":"and 40 others associated with the feud,"},{"time":832000,"text":"including hired hit men, innocent bystanders"},{"time":835000,"text":"and friends."},{"time":838000,"text":"Tensions between these two families date back to 1913"},{"time":841000,"text":"when there was a dispute over local political power."},{"time":844000,"text":"But it got violent in the last two decades"},{"time":847000,"text":"and includes decapitation"},{"time":849000,"text":"and the death of two mayors."},{"time":851000,"text":"Installed into a protective wall"},{"time":853000,"text":"surrounding the suburban home of Louis Novaes,"},{"time":856000,"text":"who's the head of the Novaes family,"},{"time":858000,"text":"are these turret holes,"},{"time":860000,"text":"which were used for shooting and looking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863000,"text":"Brazil's northeast state of Pernambuco"},{"time":866000,"text":"is one of the nation's most violent regions."},{"time":869000,"text":"It's rooted in a principle of retributive justice,"},{"time":871000,"text":"or an eye for an eye,"},{"time":873000,"text":"so retaliatory killings"},{"time":875000,"text":"have led to several deaths in the area."},{"time":878000,"text":"This story, like many of the stories in my chapters,"},{"time":881000,"text":"reads almost as an archetypal episode,"},{"time":884000,"text":"like something out of Shakespeare,"},{"time":886000,"text":"that's happening now and will happen again in the future."},{"time":889000,"text":"I'm interested in these ideas of repetition."},{"time":894000,"text":"So after I returned home, I received word"},{"time":896000,"text":"that one member of the family"},{"time":898000,"text":"had been shot 30 times in the face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"Chapter 17"},{"time":905000,"text":"is an exploration of the absence of a bloodline"},{"time":908000,"text":"and the absence of a history."},{"time":910000,"text":"Children at this Ukrainian orphanage"},{"time":912000,"text":"are between the ages of six and 16."},{"time":915000,"text":"This piece is ordered by age"},{"time":917000,"text":"because it can't be ordered by blood."},{"time":919000,"text":"In a 12-month period when I was at the orphanage,"},{"time":922000,"text":"only one child had been adopted."},{"time":925000,"text":"Children have to leave the orphanage at age 16,"},{"time":928000,"text":"despite the fact that there's often nowhere for them to go."},{"time":933000,"text":"It's commonly reported in Ukraine"},{"time":935000,"text":"that children, when leaving the orphanage"},{"time":937000,"text":"are targeted for human trafficking,"},{"time":939000,"text":"child pornography and prostitution."},{"time":942000,"text":"Many have to turn to criminal activity for their survival,"},{"time":945000,"text":"and high rates of suicide are recorded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950000,"text":"This is a boys' bedroom."},{"time":952000,"text":"There's an insufficient supply of beds at the orphanage"},{"time":954000,"text":"and not enough warm clothing."},{"time":956000,"text":"Children bathe infrequently"},{"time":958000,"text":"because the hot water isn't turned on until October."},{"time":961000,"text":"This is a girls' bedroom."},{"time":963000,"text":"And the director listed the orphanage's most urgent needs"},{"time":967000,"text":"as an industrial size washing machine and dryer,"},{"time":970000,"text":"four vacuum cleaners, two computers,"},{"time":972000,"text":"a video projector, a copy machine,"},{"time":975000,"text":"winter shoes and a dentist's drill."},{"time":978000,"text":"This photograph, which I took at the orphanage of one of the classrooms,"},{"time":982000,"text":"shows a sign which I had translated when I got home."},{"time":985000,"text":"And it reads: \"Those who do not know their past"},{"time":988000,"text":"are not worthy of their future.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":992000,"text":"There are many more chapters in this project."},{"time":994000,"text":"This is just an abridged rendering"},{"time":996000,"text":"of over a thousand images."},{"time":998000,"text":"And this mass pile of images and stories"},{"time":1001000,"text":"forms an archive."},{"time":1003000,"text":"And within this accumulation of images and texts,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"I'm struggling to find patterns"},{"time":1008000,"text":"and imagine that the narratives that surround the lives we lead"},{"time":1012000,"text":"are just as coded as blood itself."},{"time":1016000,"text":"But archives exist"},{"time":1018000,"text":"because there's something that can't necessarily be articulated."},{"time":1021000,"text":"Something is said in the gaps"},{"time":1023000,"text":"between all the information that's collected."},{"time":1026000,"text":"And there's this relentless persistence"},{"time":1029000,"text":"of birth and death"},{"time":1031000,"text":"and an unending collection of stories in between."},{"time":1034000,"text":"It's almost machine-like"},{"time":1036000,"text":"the way people are born and people die,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"and the stories keep coming and coming."},{"time":1041000,"text":"And in this, I'm considering,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"is this actual accumulation"},{"time":1046000,"text":"leading to some sort of evolution,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"or are we on repeat"},{"time":1051000,"text":"over and over again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1056000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}